    <h2>Offcanvas navigation</h2>
    <hr>

    <p>We use a lightweight offcanvas implementation with a few flexible options. These are great for mobile navigation, hidden drawers, and even alerts.</p>

    <p>You can easily set the width and height of the offcanvas areas by adjusting the <code>$offcanvas-height</code> &amp; <code>$offcanvas-width</code> variables in <code>/source/scss/modules/navigation/offcanvas.scss</code>.</p>

    <p>Add <code>class="offcanvas--push"</code> to the <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> element to push the page to the side when the left or right menu opens.</p>

    <nav class="horizontal-nav">
      <ul>
        <li class="js-open-canvas offcanvas-trigger"><a href="#oc-left" class="button">Left Offcanvas</a></li>
        <li class="js-open-canvas offcanvas-trigger"><a href="#oc-top" class="button">Top Offcanvas</a></li>
        <li class="js-open-canvas offcanvas-trigger"><a href="#oc-right" class="button">Right Offcanvas</a></li>
        <li class="js-open-canvas offcanvas-trigger"><a href="#oc-bottom" class="button">Bottom Offcanvas</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <h3>Markup example</h3>
    <pre class="line-numbers language-markup"><code>    &lt;!-- Add offcanvas--push to the body element to push page content --&gt;
    &lt;body class="offcanvas--push"&gt;
      &lt;!-- Left example. Other options are offcanvas--top, offcanvas--right, offcanvas--bottom --&gt;
      &lt;nav class="offcanvas--left" id="offcanvas"&gt;
      &lt;!-- Offcanvas content. Put anything you want in here --&gt;
      &lt;/nav&gt;

      &lt;!-- Other site content below --&gt;
      &lt;main role="main"&gt;
      &lt;!-- Point the href to the id of the offcanvas area --&gt;
      &lt;div class="js-open-canvas"&gt;&lt;a href="#offcanvas"&gt;Offcanvas toggle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/main&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;</code></pre>

